TTYCHATTER-GEMINI-PYTHON3(1)        User Commands        TTYCHATTER-GEMINI-PYTHON3(1)

NAME
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 - Bash terminal Gemini client with Python 3 helpers

SYNOPSIS
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 [session_name]
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --resume <session_name>
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --list
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --rename-session OLD NEW
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --models [--all]
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --models --sort input-tokens
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --update-models
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --test-model <model_id> [--save]
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --select-model [--save]
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --config
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --set KEY VALUE
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --unset KEY
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --set-api-key
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --forget-api-key
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --show-memory <session>
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --edit-memory <session>
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --clear-memory <session>
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --editor-prompt [session]
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --attach FILE [session]
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --credits
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --doctor
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --version
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 --help

DESCRIPTION
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 is the practical line-oriented Bash edition of
    ttychatter. It uses Bash for orchestration and Python 3 helper
    snippets for JSON, URL quoting, attachment handling, config-safe parsing,
    and other tasks that are fragile in shell alone.

    It is not the same as the Bash-only edition. This version favors reliability
    while remaining lighter than the ncurses interface.

USAGE
    First-time setup:

        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --set-api-key
        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --update-models
        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --select-model

    Start a timestamped chat:

        ttychatter-gemini-python3

    Start or reopen a named chat:

        ttychatter-gemini-python3 android-backup

    Resume a named chat:

        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --resume android-backup

    List sessions:

        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --list

    Show effective config:

        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --config

    Set config value:

        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --set CONTEXT_TURNS 20

INPUT
    Type or paste a message, then press Ctrl+D to send. Ctrl+C exits.

RUNTIME COMMAND MODE
    During a running chat, submit a line beginning with ':' to run a local
    command instead of sending a message to Gemini. Runtime commands are not
    logged as chat, not stored in memory, and not sent to Gemini.

    Common runtime commands:

        :help
            Show runtime command help.

        :quit
            Exit the running chat.

        :credits
            Show credits and Project Lead notice.

        :doctor
            Run diagnostics.

        :list
            List saved sessions.

        :rename NAME
            Rename the current session and log file.

        :models
            Show the model list.

        :update-models
            Refresh the model cache from Google.

        :select-model
            Open numbered model selector.

        :test-model MODEL
            Test one model.

        :model MODEL
            Use MODEL for the current running chat only.

        :model-save MODEL
            Use MODEL now and save it to config.

        :config
            Show current config summary.

        :set KEY VALUE
            Save config key/value.

        :unset KEY
            Remove config key.

        :set-api-key
            Prompt for and save API key.

        :forget-api-key
            Remove GEMINI_API_KEY from config.

        :memory
            Show current in-process memory/context.

        :edit-memory
            Edit current memory/context in external editor.

        :clear-memory
            Clear current memory/context.

        :attach FILE
            Attach FILE to the next Gemini message.

        :attachments
            List saved generated/code attachments.

        :editor
            Compose a prompt in external editor and send it.

    To send a literal message beginning with ':', begin it with a backslash:

        \:this goes to Gemini

MODEL WORKFLOW
    Model discovery uses the Gemini models endpoint and filters metadata rather
    than guessing future model names.

        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --models
        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --update-models
        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --test-model gemini-2.5-flash
        ttychatter-gemini-python3 --select-model

CONFIGURATION
    Shared config file:

        ~/.config/ttychatter/gemini/config

    Important keys:

        MODEL, CONTEXT_TURNS, GEMINI_API_KEY, SESSION_DIR, ATTACHMENT_DIR,
        EDITOR, MODEL_TEST_PROMPT, MAX_ATTACHMENT_BYTES, STARTUP_NOTICE,
        MODEL_FILTER_GENERATE_CONTENT, MODEL_FILTER_REQUIRE_TOKENS,
        MODEL_FILTER_HIDE_PREVIEW, MODEL_MIN_INPUT_TOKENS,
        MODEL_MIN_OUTPUT_TOKENS, MODEL_SORT_ORDER

MEMORY
    The client stores and rebuilds rolling conversation context using session
    logs and memory snapshots. CONTEXT_TURNS controls how many recent
    user/assistant exchanges are sent back to Gemini.

ATTACHMENTS
    The client can extract fenced code blocks from Gemini output into attachment
    files and can attach local files to prompts. Media support depends on model
    and API capability.

DIAGNOSTICS
    --doctor checks local readiness without printing API key values.

VERSION
    ttychatter-gemini-python3 version 3.2

AUTHOR
